         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is to study the asymptotic stability of stationary discrete shocks for the Lax-Friedrichs scheme approximating nonconvex scalar conservation laws, provided that the summations of the initial perturbations equal to zero. The result is proved by using a weighted energy method based on the nonconvexity. Moreover, the l<sup>1</sup> stability is also obtained. The key points of our proofs are to choose a suitable weight function.</p>
          </abstract>
